OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The government is set to introduce an  
OL,6, emergency law to allow people caught up
OL,7, in the Post Office scandal to have     
OL,8, their convictions overturned.          
OL,10,FPostal affairs minister Kevin          
OL,11,FHollinrake said hundreds fell victim to
OL,12,Fa "brutal and arbitrary exercise of    
OL,13,Fpower" by the Post Office.             
OL,15,FThere were more than 900 convictions   
OL,16,Flinked to the scandal over 16 years.   
OL,18,FPrime Minister Rishi Sunak told the    
OL,19,FCommons those convicted would be       
OL,20,F"swiftly exonerated and compensated".  
